Open Greedy has the following dependencies:


Dynamic linking is required with the following libraries:

SDL - http://www.libsdl.org/
Version: 2.0.3
License: zlib

SDL mixer - http://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_mixer/
Version: 2.0.0
License: zlib

zlib - http://www.zlib.net/
Version: 1.2.8
License: zlib

OpenGL - http://www.opengl.org/
Version: 1.0


Static linking is required with the following libraries:

Extended module player library lite - http://xmp.sourceforge.net/
Version: 4.3.0
License: MIT (Expat)

Basics - https://github.com/atroel/basics/
Version: 0.2
License: 2-clause BSD


Building for Linux

Open Greedy can be built under Linux using GCC and GNU Make.

Adapt Build.mk to specify where XMP-lite and Basics can be found unless they are
at the same level as Open Greedy source tree.

To build, run:
$ make


Building for Windows

Open Greedy can be built under Windows using MinGW and GNU Make.

Adapt Build.mk to specify where XMP-lite and Basics can be found unless they are
at the same level as Open Greedy source tree.

Install SDL and SDL mixer for Windows at the same level as Open Greedy source
tree (or adapt Build-Win32.mk accordingly).

To build, run:
$ make B=Win32
